org.chronos.chronodb.internal.api.query

Interface QueryTokenStream

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    StandardQueryTokenStream

    public interface QueryTokenStream
    A QueryTokenStream is a stream of QueryTokens.

    Such a stream is very similar to an Iterator<QueryToken>, except that it also allows to lookAhead() to the next token (without actually moving to the next token), and also allows to check if it isAtStartOfInput().

    • Method Detail

      • getToken

        QueryToken getToken()
             throws java.util.NoSuchElementException
        Returns the current token, and moves to the next token.
        Returns:
        The current token. Never null.
        Throws:
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - Thrown if there is no token to return, i.e. the stream has reached its end.

      • lookAhead

        QueryToken lookAhead()
              throws java.util.NoSuchElementException
        Returns the next token (i.e. the token after the one returned by getToken()) without moving away from the current token.
        Returns:
        The next token. Never null.
        Throws:
        java.util.NoSuchElementException - Thrown if there is no next token to look ahead to.

      • hasNextToken

        boolean hasNextToken()
        Checks if this stream has a next token to return.

        If this method returns true, then neither getToken() nor lookAhead() may throw an NoSuchElementException until after getToken() has been called at least once.

        Returns:
        true if there is a next token to return, false if the stream has reached its end and there are no further tokens.

      • isAtStartOfInput

        boolean isAtStartOfInput()
        Checks if the current token is the first token of the input.

        This method should return true until getToken() has been called once, and false after the first call to getToken().

        Returns:
        true if getToken() was never called on this instance, otherwise false.
